metadata.name: Where's Your Head At #4
metadata.description:
An experiment in re-creating graphic design techniques of the past using current digital methods. Halftone silkscreen printing, manual 4-colour separation and archived newspaper headlines as paste-on collages.

Headlines are taken from an actual newspaper archive, focusing on disaster and tragedy reporting.

#4 is minted on its own new collection, as per Foundation's new minting methodology.

"Someone stole my NFT."

4000 x 4000 px, 300dpi, "Scammed Out".
